ands are interactive, i.e when we passes the input to the kernel, we will get valid response from kernel. if we are sending sequence of commands in certain file( say text file) &amp; try to execute , we will get a response or output from the kernel. This set of instructions or commands is called shell script.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Shell scripts are more powerful unlike MS DOS batch file (cmd files).</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Different Types of Shells:-</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nIn Linux widley used different types of shells are\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Bash or Bourne Shell,</li>\r\n	<li>K shell</li>\r\n	<li>C Shell.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nBash Shell is developed by Brain Fox and Chet Ramey which is popular among all the shells. Csh or C shell is similar to C programming language developed by Bill Joy. And KSh or Korn Shell is developed by David Korn.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>', 'What is Shells in Linux - Intro', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'intro-of-shells', '', '', '2016-01-15 01:57:50', '2016-01-14 20:27:50', '', '0', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/?p=16', '0', 'post', '', '0' ); ";i:566;s:1210:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '17', '1', '2015-12-15 23:22:18', '2015-12-15 17:52:18', '\r\n\r\nThis is an example page. Its different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\r\n\r\nHi there! Im a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pia coladas. (And gettin caught in the rain.)\r\nor something like this:\r\n\r\nThe XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.\r\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'All About Shells', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-15 23:22:18', '2015-12-15 17:52:18', '', '16', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2015/12/15/16-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:567;s:277:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '19', '1', '2015-12-16 01:12:49', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'Home', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2015-12-16 01:12:49', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/?p=19', '1', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0' ); ";i:568;s:1271:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '23', '1', '2015-12-16 01:25:00', '2015-12-15 19:55:00', 'thatisLinux.com helps you in knowing about the Linux basics to advanced topics &amp; also great tutorials.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\nOverview:-\r\n</strong>\r\nWe concentrate on the simple to major installation of software\'s that are used in current software web development projects such as\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Software development tools for the website</li>\r\n	<li> Linux administration scripts &amp; Ideas</li>\r\n	<li> Cloud computing</li>\r\n	<li> Networking/DNS/Firewalls</li>\r\n	<li> Best Practices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSimple tutorials in layman English helps you in understanding well about the topics which is self explanatory with lot of screen shots.\r\n\r\nConnect us on<a href=\"https://plus.google.com/u/0/111641777437636327729/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"author\">Google Plus</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a>or <a href=\"http://localhost/thatislinux.com/contact/\">contact </a>us in the contact form.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2016-01-13 03:48:35', '2016-01-12 22:18:35', '', '0', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/?page_id=23', '0', 'page', '', '0' ); ";i:569;s:1318:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '24', '1', '2015-12-16 01:25:00', '2015-12-15 19