mong all the shells. Csh or C shell is similar to C programming language developed by Bill Joy. And KSh or Korn Shell is developed by David Korn.</span></p></div><div><br /></div>', 'All About Shells', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-30 00:20:16', '2015-12-29 18:50:16', '', '16', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2015/12/30/16-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:615;s:6034:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '78', '1', '2015-12-30 00:23:51', '2015-12-29 18:53:51', '<div><strong><span style=\"font-size:20px;font-family:Times New Roman;text-decoration:underline\">How to Install HTTPD Apache web server:-</span></strong></div><div><br /></div><div><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\">To Install using YUM package:-</span></strong></p></div><div><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\"> [Example.com]#yum install httpd </span></article><article><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> or </span></article><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\"> [Example.com]#up2date httpd</span></article><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"></span></article><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><br /></article></div><div><span style=\"color:#333399;font-size:18px;font-family:Times New Roman\"><strong>Install using Standard way:-</strong></span></div><div><br /></div><div><article><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Download the required tar file - either httpd 2.2 or httpd 2.4 version which are currently available in the Apache site</span></article><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">lets download httpd-2.2.31.tar.gz in the /opt drive</span><br /></div><div><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">1. Extract the gz file</span></article></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> </span><span style=\"background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\">[Example.com]# tar -xvzf httpd-2.2.31.tar.gz </span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff\">  </span><span style=\"background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\">[Example.com]# cd httpd-2.2.31</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">2. Configure</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399\">[Example.com]#./configure --prefix=PREFIX [ Include what ever the configuration or specs needed]</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\">  </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\">for example --enable-rewrite=shared --enable-speling=shared</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">3. Compile</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#F2F0F5\">[Example.com]# make</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">4. Install</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#F2F0F5\">[Example.com]# make install</span></div><div><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p></div><div><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:16px\">Start the Apache:-</span></strong></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399\">[Example.com]# /etc/init.d/httpd start</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">or</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"></span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399\">[Example.com]#apachetl -k start</span></div><div><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p></div><div><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:16px\">To Stop :-</span></strong></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#F2F0F5\">[Example.com]# /etc/init.d/httpd stop</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">or</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#F2F0F5\">[Example.com]#apachetl -k stop</span></div><div><p><wbr /><br /></p></div><div><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Times New Roman\">Permanent Configuration:-</span></strong></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#F2F0F5\">[Example.com]# chkconfig httpd on</span></div><div><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p></div><div><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">To check whether it is running or not:-</span></strong></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#ffffff\"> </span><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#333399;background-color:#F2F0F5\">[Example.com]# netstat -tulpn | grep :80</span></div><div><br /></div><div><p>&nbsp;</p><article><strong><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Further configuration:-</span></strong></article></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Check the </span><a href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/\" style=\"color:#0000ff;font-family:Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Apache website</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> for detailed configuration about the httpd.conf as per your requirements</span></div><div><br /></div>', 'How to install Apache HTTPD', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '47-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-30 00:23:51', '2015-12-29 18:53:51', '', '47', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2015/12/30/47-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:616;s:5854:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '79', '1', '2015-12-30 08:20:33', '2015-12-30 02:50:33', '<div><br /></div><div><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\">To Install using YUM package:-</span></strong></p></div><div><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\"> [Example.com]#yum install httpd </span></article><article><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> or </span></article><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\"> [Example.com]#up2date httpd</span></article><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"></span></article><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><br /></article></div><div><span style=\"color:#333399;font-size:18px;font-family:Times New Roman\"><strong>Install using Standard way:-</strong></span></div><div><br /></div><div><article><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Download the required tar file - either httpd 2.2 or httpd 2.4 version which are currently available in the Apache site</span></article><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">lets download httpd-2.2.31.tar.gz in the /opt drive</span><br /></div><div><article style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">1. Extract the gz file</span></article></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\"> </span><span style=\"background-color:#F2F0F5;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman\">[Example.com]# tar -xvz