derline; color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Installation of YUM package using CD/DVD ISO<!--more Read More!--> image:-</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong> <span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Times New Roman;\">Step 1</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Times New Roman;\">: Mount the DVD/CD in the mnt</span>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com#] mount /dev/dvdwriter /mnt</pre>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Times New Roman;\"><strong>Step 2:</strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Times New Roman;\"> Create Repo file in /etc/repos.d/</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Times New Roman;\">.repo</span>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com#] vim /etc/repos.d/serverRepo.repo</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<article style=\"line-height: 120%; direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">[ServerRepo] name=Linux DVD ISO</span></article><article style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\"> baseurl=file:///mnt </span></article><article style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">enabled=1 </span></article><article style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">gpgcheck=1 </span></article><article style=\"line-height: 120%; direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">gpgkey=file:///mnt/RPM-GPG-KEY-CentOS-6</span></article><span style=\"color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\"></span><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; ;color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\">Lets see the other way of installation of YUM:-</span></strong><span style=\"color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\">\r\n</span>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Download the yum package from any of the linux kernels, say for example yum-2.0.7.tar.gz </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Untar the file yum-2.0.7.tar.gz </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# tar -xvzf yum-2.0.7.tar.gz</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Run the configuration file after extracting</span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# ./configure</pre>\r\nMake Configuration\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# make</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Make installation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# make install</pre>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Installation of  YUM Package', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-08 02:29:28', '2016-01-07 20:59:28', '', '54', 'http://lo