ection: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">enabled=1 </span></article><article style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">gpgcheck=1 </span></article><article style=\"line-height: 120%; direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">gpgkey=file:///mnt/RPM-GPG-KEY-CentOS-6</span></article><span style=\"color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\"></span><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; ;color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\">Lets see the other way of installation of YUM:-</span></strong><span style=\"color: #666699; font-size: 18px;\">\r\n</span>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Download the yum package from any of the linux kernels, say for example yum-2.0.7.tar.gz </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Untar the file yum-2.0.7.tar.gz </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# tar -xvzf yum-2.0.7.tar.gz</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Run the configuration file after extracting</span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# ./configure</pre>\r\nMake Configuration\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# make</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Make installation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# make install</pre>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Installation of  YUM Package', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-08 02:30:30', '2016-01-07 21:00:30', '', '54', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/08/54-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:698;s:2348:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '163', '1', '2016-01-08 02:31:04', '2016-01-07 21:01:04', '<div><p><span style=\"font-size:20px;color:#000080;font-family:Times New Roman\">What is Shell:-</span></p></div><div><p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Shell is a special interpreter or program in the operating System which is used to communicate between user commands and the computer/kernel.Shell passes the<!--more Continue Reading!-->  command to the kernel via keyboard or file.</span></p><p></p></div><div>\r\n</div><div><p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000080;font-size:20px\">Shell Script:-</span></p></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Shells or commands are interactive, i.e when we passes the input to the kernel, we will get valid response from kernel. if we are sending sequence of commands in certain file( say text file) &amp; try to execute , we will get a response or output from the kernel. This set of instructions or commands is called shell script.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Shell scripts are more powerful unlike MS DOS batch file (cmd files).</span></div><div><p><br /></p></div><div><p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000080;font-size:20px\">Different Types of Shells:-</span></p></div><div><p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">In Linux widley used different types of shells are </span></p><p></p><ol><li style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Times New Roman\">Bash or Bourne Shell, </span></li><li style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Times New Roman\">K shell</span></li><li style=\"line-height:100%\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Times New Roman\"> C Shell.&nbsp;</span></li></ol><p></p><p><span style=\"font-family:Times New Roman\">Bash Shell is developed by Brain Fox and Chet Ramey which is popular among all the shells. Csh or C shell is similar to C programming language developed by Bill Joy. And KSh or Korn Shell is developed by David Korn.</span></p></div><div><br /></div>', 'All About Shells', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-08 02:31:04', '2016-01-07 21:01:04', '', '16', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/08/16-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:699;s:6152:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '164', '1', '2016-01-08 02:31:32', '2016-01-07 21:01:32', '\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: #333399; font-family: Times New Roman;\">To Install using YUM package:-</span></strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><article style=\"line-height: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; background-color: #f2f0f5; color: #333399; font-family: Times New Roman;\"> <!--more Continue Reading!--> [Example.com]#yum install httpd </span></article><article><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"> or </span></article><article style=\"line-height: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; background-color: #f2f0f5; color: #333399; font-family: Times New Roman;\"> [Example.com]#up2date httpd</span></article><article style=\"line-height: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"></span></article><article style=\"line-height: 100%;\"></article></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"color: #333399; font-size: 18px; font-family: Times New Roman;\"><strong>Install using Standard way:-</strong></span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><artic