div>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[Example.com]# tar -xvzf httpd-2.2.31.tar.gz </pre>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[Example.com]# cd httpd-2.2.31<pre>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">2. Configure</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; background-color: #f2f0f5; color: #333399;\">[Example.com]#./configure --prefix=PREFIX [ Include what ever the configuration or specs needed]</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\">  </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\">for example --enable-rewrite=shared --enable-speling=shared</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">3. Compile</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #f2f0f5;\">[Example.com]# make</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">4. Install</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #f2f0f5;\">[Example.com]# make install</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">Start the Apache:-</span></strong></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; background-color: #f2f0f5; color: #333399;\">[Example.com]# /etc/init.d/httpd start</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">or</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"></span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; background-color: #f2f0f5; color: #333399;\">[Example.com]#apachetl -k start</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px;\">To Stop :-</span></strong></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #f2f0f5;\">[Example.com]# /etc/init.d/httpd stop</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">or</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #f2f0f5;\">[Example.com]#apachetl -k stop</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<wbr />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Times New Roman;\">Permanent Configuration:-</span></strong></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #f2f0f5;\">[Example.com]# chkconfig httpd on</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">To check whether it is running or not:-</span></strong></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #ffffff;\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; color: #333399; background-color: #f2f0f5;\">[Example.com]# netstat -tulpn | grep :80</span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<article><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Further configuration:-</span></strong></article></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Check the </span><a style=\"color: #0000ff; font-family: Times New Roman;\" href=\"https://httpd.apache.org/\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\">Apache website</span></a><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"> for detailed configuration about the httpd.conf as per your requirements</span></div>\r\n<div></div>', 'How to install Apache HTTPD', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '47-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-10 00:35:14', '2016-01-09 19:05:14', '', '47', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/10/47-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:707;s:6521:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '172', '1', '2016-01-10 09:27:38', '2016-01-10 03:57:38', 'How to Install Apache HTTPD WEB Server in the linux platform?\r\n\r\nApache HTTPD server is a free-open source web server software which is widely used in Linux/Unix kind of operating systems.\r\n\r\n<!--more Continue Reading-->\r\n\r\nThe Goal of this server is to provide secure, efficient and extensible way by which it provides all HTTP Standards &amp; Services.\r\n\r\nThe latest version of Apache HTTPD Server in market is <a href=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/\">HTTPD 2.4</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: #333399; font-family: Times New Roman;\">To Install using YUM package:-</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe can install apache httpd server using yum command for Redhat Linux or also using below command for other flavours of Linux, Below command will install httpd2.0.* version which ever is yum repository configured.\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[Example.com]#yum install httpd</pre>\r\nor\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[Example.com]#up2date httpd</pre>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"color: #333399; font-size: 18px; font-family: Times New Roman;\"><strong>Install using Standard way:-</strong></span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a