Linux', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-14 22:58:30', '2016-01-14 17:28:30', '', '16', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/14/16-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:717;s:3336:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '182', '1', '2016-01-14 23:50:33', '2016-01-14 18:20:33', '<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">YUM is the core package which is used for installing, updating, removing &amp; finding the packages. Basically YUM Is referred as<strong>YellowDog Updater Modified</strong> which <!--more Continue Reading!--> is developed by Redhat. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-size: 18px;\"><strong>Installation of YUM package using CD/DVD ISO image:-</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 1: Mount the DVD/CD in the mnt\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com#] mount /dev/dvdwriter /mnt</pre>\r\nStep 2: Create Repo file in /etc/repos.d/<name>.repo\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com#] vim /etc/repos.d/serverRepo.repo</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<pre style=\"line-height: 120%; direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">[ServerRepo] name=Linux DVD ISO</span></pre>\r\n<pre style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\"> baseurl=file:///mnt </span></pre>\r\n<pre style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">enabled=1 </span></pre>\r\n<pre style=\"direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px; line-height: 120%;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">gpgcheck=1 </span></pre>\r\n<pre style=\"line-height: 120%; direction: ltr; margin-left: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 16px; color: #000080; background-color: #ffffff;\">gpgkey=file:///mnt/RPM-GPG-KEY-CentOS-6</span></pre>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"></span></h4>\r\n<h3>Lets see the other way of installation of YUM:-</h3>\r\nDownload the yum package from any of the linux kernels, say for example yum-2.0.7.tar.gz.Untar the file\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# tar -xvzf yum-2.0.7.tar.gz</pre>\r\nRun the configuration file after extracting\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# ./configure</pre>\r\nMake Configuration\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# make</pre>\r\nMake installation\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">[example.com]# make install</pre>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Installation of  YUM Package', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-14 23:50:33', '2016-01-14 18:20:33', '', '54', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/14/54-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:718;s:5104:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '183', '1', '2016-01-15 02:41:22', '2016-01-14 21:11:22', 'Installation of Apache ant involves easy steps. Download the required version of ANT from the Apache ANT downloads page,<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"https://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\">Apache ANT</span> </a></span>, Lets choose the latest version<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://download.nextag.com/apache//ant/binaries/apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\">ant-1.9.6</a></span></span><!--more Continue Reading-->\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDownload the ant binary filein /opt/ directory using WGET command\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># wget http://download.nextag.com/apache//ant/binaries/apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\n\r\n--2016-01-14 20:49:37-- http://download.nextag.com/apache//ant/binaries/apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\nResolving download.nextag.com (download.nextag.com)... 216.185.212.50\r\nConnecting to download.nextag.com (download.nextag.com)|216.185.212.50|:80... connected.\r\nHTTP request sent, awaiting response... 200 OK\r\nLength: 5588888 (5.3M) [application/x-gzip]\r\nSaving to: apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\n\r\napache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz 100%[=================================&gt;] 5.33M 3.21MB/s in 1.7s\r\n\r\n2016-01-14 20:49:39 (3.21 MB/s) - apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz saved [5588888/5588888]\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Extract the file using tar command,</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># tar -xvzf apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\napache-ant-1.9.6/bin/ant\r\napache-ant-1.9.6/bin/antRun\r\napache-ant-1.9.6/bin/antRun.pl\r\napache-ant-1.9.6/bin/complete-ant-cmd.pl\r\napache-ant-1.9.6/bin/runant.pl\r\napache-ant-1.9.6/bin/runant.py\r\n..............\r\n</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Delete the .gz file to save the disk space</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># rm -fapache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\n</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSetting the <strong>ENVIRONMENTAL variables for ANT To work. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">JDK 1.7 is the perquisite before installing ANT</span>\r\n</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">export ANT_HOME=/usr/local/ant\r\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/jdk1.8.0_91\r\nexport PATH=${PATH}:${ANT_HOME}/bin\r\n</pre>\r\nAbove needs to be set either in the .bashrc file or /etc/profile file.\r\n\r\nAfter setting the environmental path, we can try executing the below command to check whether ant is executable from the shell,\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># ant\r\nBuildfile: build.xml does not exist!\r\nBuild failed\r\n</pre>\r\nthis mean installation is successful!!!!!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong> We need to run the below command to upgrade the ant library to latest,</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># ant -f fetch.xml -Ddest=system</pre>\r\nthis is used to get the library dependencies to execute the run.\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># ant -f fetch.xml -Ddest=system\r\nBuildfile: /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/fetch.xml\r\n\r\npick-dest:\r\n[echo] Downloading to /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/lib\r\n\r\nprobe-m2:\r\n\r\ndownload-m2:\r\n[echo] Downloading to /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/lib\r\n[get] Getting: http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/maven-artifact-ant/2.0.4/maven-artifact-ant-2.0.4-dep.jar\r\n[get] To: /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/lib/maven-artifact-ant-2.0.4-dep.jar\r\n[get] ....................................................\r\n[get] ................................\r\n\r\ndont-validate-m2-checksum:\r\n...........\r\n...........\r\ninit-cache:\r\n\r\n-cleanup-temp-cache:\r\n\r\nall:\r\n\r\nBUILD SUCCESSFUL\r\nTotal time: 7 seconds\r\n</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>To check the ANT Version:-</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># ant -version\r\nApache Ant(TM) version 1.9.6 compiled on June 29 2015\r\n</pre>\r\nNow its ready to use the ANT scripts for ANT Tasks.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'How to Install Apache ANT in LINUX', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-install-apache-ant-in-linux', '', '', '2016-01-15 02:43:39', '2016-01-14 21:13:39', '', '0', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/?p=183', '0', 'post', '', '0' ); ";i:719;s:1437:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '184', '1', '2016-01-14 23:59:34', '2016-01-14 18:29:34', 'export ANT_HOME=/usr/local/ant\r\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/jdk1.7.0_51\r\nexport PATH=${PATH}:${ANT_HOME}/bin\r\n\r\n\r\nMake sure you have a Java environment installed, See System Requirements for details.\r\nDownload Ant. See Binary Edition for details.\r\nUncompress the downloaded file into a directory.\r\nSet environmental variables JAVA_HOME to your Java environment, ANT_HOME to the directory you uncompressed Ant to, and add ${ANT_HOME}/bin (Unix) or %ANT_HOME%/bin (Windows) to your PATH. See Setup for details.\r\nOptionally, from the ANT_HOME directory run ant -f fetch.xml -Ddest=system to get the library dependencies of most of the Ant tasks that require them. If you don\'t do this, many of the dependent Ant tasks will not be available. See Optional Tasks for details and other options for the -Ddest parameter.\r\nOptionally, add any desired Antlibs. See Ant Libraries for a list.\r\n\r\n\r\ncat >> /etc/profile.d/extrapaths.sh << EOF\r\n\r\n# Begin Apache-ant addition\r\n\r\npathappend /opt/ant/bin\r\nexport ANT_HOME=/opt/ant\r\n\r\n# End Apache-ant addition\r\n\r\nEOF', 'How to Install Apache ANT in LINUX', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-14 23:59:34', '2016-01-14 18:29:34', '', '183', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/14/183-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:720;s:490:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '185', '1', '2016-01-15 00:01:00', '2016-01-14 18:31:00', '', 'How to Install Firefox in Linux', '<p>asdasdadsasdsad</p><p>asdasd</p><p>sad</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>asd</p><p>dsa</p><p>dsa</p><p>sa</p><p>sa</p><p>da</p><p>dasd</p><p>as</p><p>d&nbsp;</p>', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '160-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-15 00:01:00', '2016-01-14 18:31:00', '', '160', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/15/160-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:721;s:302:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '186', '1', '2016-01-15 00:01:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'How to Install Headless Firefox in Linux', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2016-01-15 00:01:15', '2016-01-14 18:31:15', '', '0', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/?p=186', '0', 'post', '', '0' ); ";i:722;s:350:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '187', '1', '2016-01-15 00:01:15', '2016-01-14 18:31:15', '', 'How to Install Headless Firefox in Linux', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '186-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-15 00:01:15', '2016-01-14 18:31:15', '', '186', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/15/186-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:723;s:290:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '188', '1', '2016-01-15 00:01:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'How to Install Solr in Linux', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2016-01-15 00:01:52', '2016-01-14 18:31:52', '', '0', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/?p=188', '0', 'post', '', '0' ); ";i:724;s:338:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '189', '1', '2016-01-15 00:01:52', '2016-01-14 18:31:52', '', 'How to Install Solr in Linux', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-15 00:01:52', '2016-01-14 18:31:52', '', '188', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/15/188-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:725;s:304:"INSERT INTO wp_posts 