</Strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">\r\n# rm -fapache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\n</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSetting the <strong>ENVIRONMENTAL variables for ANT To work. JDK 1.7 is the perquisite before installing ANT\r\n</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">\r\nexport ANT_HOME=/usr/local/ant\r\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/jdk1.8.0_91\r\nexport PATH=${PATH}:${ANT_HOME}/bin\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nAbove needs to be set either in the .bashrc file or /etc/profile file.\r\n\r\nAfter setting the environmental path, we can try executing the below command to check whether ant is executable from the shell,\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">\r\n# ant\r\nBuildfile: build.xml does not exist!\r\nBuild failed\r\n</pre>\r\nthis mean installation is successful.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong> We need to run the below command to upgrade the ant library to latest,</strong>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># ant -f fetch.xml -Ddest=system</pre>\r\n\r\nthis is used to get the library dependencies to execute the run.\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># ant -f fetch.xml -Ddest=system\r\nBuildfile: /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/fetch.xml\r\n\r\npick-dest:\r\n[echo] Downloading to /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/lib\r\n\r\nprobe-m2:\r\n\r\ndownload-m2:\r\n[echo] Downloading to /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/lib\r\n[get] Getting: http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/maven-artifact-ant/2.0.4/maven-artifact-ant-2.0.4-dep.jar\r\n[get] To: /opt/apache-ant-1.9.6/lib/maven-artifact-ant-2.0.4-dep.jar\r\n[get] ....................................................\r\n[get] ................................\r\n\r\ndont-validate-m2-checksum:\r\n.....\r\ninit-cache:\r\n\r\n-cleanup-temp-cache:\r\n\r\nall:\r\n\r\nBUILD SUCCESSFUL\r\nTotal time: 7 seconds\r\n</pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>To check the ANT Version</strong>\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\">\r\n# ant -version\r\nApache Ant(TM) version 1.9.6 compiled on June 29 2015\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nNow its ready to use the ANT scripts for ANT Tasks.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'How to Install Apache ANT in LINUX', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-15 02:36:54', '2016-01-14 21:06:54', '', '183', 'http://localhost/thatislinux.com/2016/01/15/183-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0' ); ";i:745;s:5156:"INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES( '210', '1', '2016-01-15 02:39:07', '2016-01-14 21:09:07', '<h2>How to Install Apache ANT in Linux</h2>\r\nInstallation of Apache ant involves easy steps. Download the required version of ANT from the Apache ANT downloads page,<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"https://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\">Apache ANT</span> </a></span>, Lets choose the latest version<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\"><a style=\"color: #0000ff; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://download.nextag.com/apache//ant/binaries/apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\">ant-1.9.6</a></span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDownload the ant binary filein /opt/ directory using WGET command\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #595353; font-family: Georgia; color: #f0ebeb; font-weight: 500; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal;\"># wget http://download.nextag.com/apache//ant/binaries/apache-ant-1.9.6-bin.tar.gz\r\n\r\n--2016-01-14 20:49:37-- http://download.nextag.com/apache//ant/binaries/apa